<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1204,1663]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1240,1266]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
From the original description: “Small, elongate, subovate… Antennae elongate and slender, nearly twice as long as the body… third segment shorter than scape… Pronotum transverse, almost parallel-sided, bearing on each side at about the basal quarter a small, slender, almost porrect, acute spine… Elytra elongate subovate; apices obliquely-truncate, sutural angle rounded, marginal about rectangular; disc smooth, feebly depressed premedially. Prosternal process fairly narrow, about a quarter the breadth of a procoxal cavity… mesosternal process narrow, narrowing to the apex, narrower than the prosternal, narrowly rounded apically…” Number of species currently included: 2 (both from 
<collectingCountry box="[411,497,1456,1482]" name="Mexico" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and Central 
<taxonomicName box="[639,741,1456,1483]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="America" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="334" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">America</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="320" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,1204,1663]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1493,1519]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Remarks.</emphasis>
Unfortunately, 
<bibRefCitation author="Gilmour, E. F." box="[491,680,1492,1519]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="329 - 341" refId="ref21705" refString="Gilmour, E. F. (1959 a) On the Neotropical Acanthocinini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). New genera and species from Mexico. Anales del Instituto de Biologia, 29 (1 - 2), 329 - 341." type="journal article" year="1959">Gilmour (1959a)</bibRefCitation>
did not inform if the row of punctures on transverse basal sulcus of the pronotum continues or not laterally behind the lateral tubercles of the prothorax. However, as he knew very well the difference between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bates" authorityYear="1863" box="[412,523,1565,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturges" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[412,523,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Lepturges</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dillon" authorityYear="1956" box="[576,685,1564,1590]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Urgleptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,685,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Urgleptes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Gilmour, E. F." box="[744,920,1564,1591]" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" pagination="1 - 10" refId="ref21832" refString="Gilmour, E. F. (1959 d) On the Neotropical Acanthocinini V (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). New species of Lepturges Bates and Urgleptes Dillon. Opuscula Zoologica, 28, 1 - 10." type="journal article" year="1959">Gilmour 1959d</bibRefCitation>
), probably the punctures do not follow toward sides of the prothorax. If the punctures follow toward sides of the prothorax, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gilmour" authorityYear="1959" box="[1015,1149,1601,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Lepturginus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1015,1149,1601,1626]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Lepturginus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dillon" authorityYear="1956" box="[182,291,1636,1662]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Urgleptes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="320" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[182,291,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="320">Urgleptes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
